		<div class="span-9 last">	

			<h3><span class="alt">3D Rasterization</span> in the Flash Player</h3>
			
			These demos demonstrate the ability of the Flash Player to render relatively high quality 3D graphics
			when the appropriate transform, lighting and rasterization algorithms are implemented.
			<br><br>
			In order to get the best performance possible I wrote these demos entirely in C++ which is then compiled to ActionScript 3
			using the <a href="http://labs.adobe.com/technologies/alchemy/">Alchemy</a> toolchain. There is a small AS3 based host that loads the compiled .swc (code library that Alchemy produces)
			file in each demo.
			<br><br>
			Please note that in all demos full perspective correction is being done per pixel. All the scenes are fully dynamic,
			lighting is as noted in the demo description.
			<br><br>
			There are 0 (zero) calls to DrawTriangles in these demos!
			
